9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 769, L.D. 1164, “An Act to Create
10 Economic Opportunity for the Wabanaki Nations Through Internet Gaming”
11 Amend the bill in section 4 in c. 39 in §1416 by striking out all of subsection 1 (page
12 17, lines 5 to 23 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 '1. Tax imposed; allocation of funds. An operator shall collect and distribute 18%
14 of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts to the director to be forwarded by the director
15 to the Treasurer of State for distribution as follows:
16 A. Two percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be deposited in the
17 Gambling Control Unit administrative expenses Other Special Revenue Funds account,
18 which is a nonlapsing dedicated account;
19 B. Two percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be deposited in the
20 Gambling Addiction Prevention and Treatment Fund established under Title 5, section
21 20006‑B;
22 C. Two and one-half percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be
23 deposited in the dairy stabilization tier program under Title 7, chapter 611;
24 D. One and one-half percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be
25 deposited in the Opioid Use Disorder Prevention and Treatment Fund established under
26 Title 5, section 20010;
27 E. Two percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be deposited in the
28 Emergency Housing Relief Fund established under Title 30-A, section 4765;
29 F. Five percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be deposited in the
30 Maine Veterans' Homes Stabilization Fund established under Title 37-B, section 613;
31 G. One percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be deposited in the
32 Fund for a Healthy Maine established under Title 22, section 1511; and
33 H. Two percent of the adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts must be deposited in the
34 School Revolving Renovation Fund established under Title 30-A, section 6006-F.'
