22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment adjusts the allocation of funds for adjusted gross Internet gaming
2266 receipts. The amendment increases the overall collection and distribution of adjusted gross
2277 Internet gaming receipts from 16% to 18%. It makes the following changes to distribution
2288 of adjusted gross Internet gaming receipts.
29 1. It reduces from 3% to 2% the amount that must be deposited in the Gambling
30 Addiction Prevention and Treatment Fund and reduces from 3% to 1.5% the amount that
31 must be deposited in the Opioid Use Disorder Prevention and Treatment Fund.
32 2. It increases from 3% to 5% the amount that must be deposited in the Maine Veterans’
33 Homes Stabilization Fund.
34 3. It adds a 2.5% deposit to the dairy stabilization tier program, a 1% deposit into the
35 Fund for a Healthy Maine and a 2% deposit in the School Revolving Renovation Fund.
36 4. It removes the E-9-1-1 fund from the list of entities receiving funds.
37 5. It makes no changes to the distribution of 2% to the Emergency Housing Relief Fund
38 or to the distribution of 2% to the Gambling Control Unit administrative expenses Other
39 Special Revenue Funds account.
